<li>Shelley, Cameron, 2003. &ldquo;Aspects of visual argument: A study
of the &lsquo;March of Progress&rsquo;,&rdquo; <em>Informal
Logic</em>, 21(2): 92&ndash;112.</li>

<li>Sobocan, Jan (ed.), 2021. <em>Critical Thinking, Education and
Assessment: Can Critical Thinking Be Tested?</em>, 2nd ed. Windsor:
Windsor Studies in Argument.</li>

<li>Stevens, Katharina and Daniel Cohen, 2019. &ldquo;The attraction
of the ideal has no traction on the real: on adversariality and roles
in argument,&rdquo; <em>Argumentation and Advocacy</em>, 55(1):
1&ndash;23.</li>

<li>St&ouml;ckl, Hartmut, Assimakis Tseronis, and Janina Wildfeuer,
eds. 2025. <em>Arguing with Multiple Semiotic Modes</em>. Theoretical
Issues and Empirical Advances in Multimodal Argumentation Studies
(Pathways to Multimodality 3). Berlin/Boston: de Gruyter.</li>

<li>St&ouml;ckl, Hartmut and Assimakis Tseroni, 2023.
&ldquo;Multimodal rhetoric and argumentation,&rdquo; <em>Journal of
Argumentation in Context</em>, 13(2): 167&ndash;176.
 <a href="https://doi.org/10.1075/jaic.00026.tse"></a>.</li>
 
<li>Thagard, Paul, 2011.
 &ldquo;<a href="http://doi.org/10.22329/il.v31i3.3398" target="other">Critical Thinking and Informal Logic: Neuropsychological Perspectives,</a>&rdquo;
 <em>Informal Logic</em>, 31(3): 152&ndash;70.</li>

<li>Tindale, Christopher W., 2025. &ldquo;The Rhetorical Perspective
on Argumentation,&rdquo; in Aiken, Casey, and Stevens, <em>The
Routledge Handbook of Argumentation</em>. London: Routledge.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2021. <em>The Anthropology of Argument:
Cultural Foundations of Rhetoric and Reason</em>, New York:
Routledge.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010. <em>Reason&rsquo;s Dark Champions:
Constructive Strategies of Sophistic Argument</em>, Columbia: South
Carolina Press.</li>

<li>Toulmin, Stephen, 1958 [2n ed., 2003]. <em>The Uses of
Argument</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press; revised edition,
2003.</li>

<li>Tseronis, Assimakis and Charles Forceville, eds. 2017.
<em>Multimodal Argumentation and Rhetoric in Media Genres,</em>
(Argumentation in Context, Volume 14), Amsterdam: John Benjamins.</li>

<li>Verheij, Bart, 2014. &ldquo;Argumentation and Artificial
Intelligence,&rdquo; Chapter 11 in Eemeren et al., 2014.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999. &ldquo;Automated Argument Assistance
for Lawyers,&rdquo; <em>Proceedings of the Seventh International
Conference on Artificial Intelligence and Law</em>, New York:
Association of Computing Machinery, pp. 43&ndash;52.</li>

<li>Walton, Douglas N., 2012. &ldquo;Story similarity in arguments
from analogy,&rdquo; <em>Informal Logic</em>, 32: 190&ndash;221.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007. <em>Dialog Theory for Critical
Argumentation</em>, Amsterdam: John Benjamins Publishing Company.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2004. <em>Abductive Reasoning</em>,
Tuscaloosa, University of Alabama Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000. <em>Scare Tactics: Arguments that
Appeal to Fear and Threats</em> (Argumentation Library: Volume 3),
Berlin: Springer.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1989. <em>Informal Logic: A Handbook for
Critical Argumentation</em>, New York: Cambridge University
Press.</li>

<li>Walton, Douglas and Erik C.W. Krabbe, 1995. <em>Commitment in
Dialogue: Basic Concepts of Interpersonal Reasoning</em>. Albany:
State University of New York Press.</li>

<li>Walton, Douglas, Christopher Reed, Fabrizio Macagno, 2008.
<em>Argumentation Schemes</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University
Press.</li>

<li>Weston, Anthony, 2018. <em>A Rulebook for Arguments</em>, 5th ed.,
Indianapolis: Hackett.</li>

<li>Whately, Richard, 1826.
 <a href="https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015063020500&amp;view;=image&amp;seq;=" target="other"><em>Elements of logic</em></a>,
 London: B. Fellowes.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1830. <em>Elements of rhetoric</em>, 3rd
edition, Oxford: W. Baxter.</li>

<li>Wigmore, John Henry, 1913. <em>The principles of judicial proof:
as given by logic, psychology, and general experience, and illustrated
in judicial trials</em>, Boston: Little Brown.</li>

<li>Wilson, David Carl, 2020. <em>A Guide to Good Reasoning:
Cultivating Intellectual Virtues</em>, 2nd edition, Twin Cities:
University of Minesota Libraries.</li>

<li>Woods, John and Douglas Walton 1982. <em>Argument: The Logic of
the Fallacies</em>, Roronto: McGraw-Hill Ryerson.</li>

<li>Woods, John, 2000. &ldquo;How Philosophical is Informal Logic?
&rdquo; <em>Informal Logic</em>, 20(2): 139&ndash;167.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1995. &ldquo;Appeal to Force,&rdquo; in
Hansen and Pinto 1995, pp. 240&ndash;250.</li>

<li>Zenker, F. 2013. <em>Bayesian Argumentation: The practical side of
probability</em> (Synthese Library 362), Dordrecht: Springer.</li>
</ul>
</div> 

